      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MR. EINSTEIN (2) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 1.75 lengths win at this track in a handy 25.63. Draws to advantage and likes the trip. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from four starts. Can measure up again. FOR MERCY SAKE (7) is better than last start when seventh (28.39) in a Grade 5 at Casino over 484m. Has a good record here including two wins. Expected to feature in the finish. BROWN BREAD (3) was in winning form two back (23.25) at Casino but ran below best last time there, finishing 7th. Can do much better this time. WITCHY WOMAN (1) must be included in calculations.",
